sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant FE as browser
    participant GW as api-gateway
    participant AUTH as orches-auth-service
    participant SVC as user-service
    participant DB as user-db
    participant R as Redis

    Note over FE,R: Pre-state: login:softlock:{userId} auto-expired in Redis<br/>failed_login_attempts = 5 in DB — NOT reset by expiry   hard_locked = false

    rect rgb(240,248,255)
    Note over FE,R: 1. Login & Pre-checks

    FE->>GW: POST /auth/login { email, password }
    GW->>AUTH: login({ email, password })
    AUTH->>SVC: find_user_by_email(email)
    SVC->>DB: SELECT id, is_email_verified, password_hash,<br/>failed_login_attempts, hard_locked<br/>FROM users WHERE email = ? AND deleted_at IS NULL
    DB-->>SVC: { failed_login_attempts: 5, hard_locked: false, ... }
    SVC-->>AUTH: user

    AUTH->>R: EXISTS login:softlock:{userId}
    R-->>AUTH: 0 (key expired — no active lock)
    Note over AUTH: lock expired — failed_login_attempts = 5 still in DB, NOT reset
    end

    rect rgb(255,248,235)
    Note over FE,R: 2. Credential Validation

    Note over AUTH: bcrypt.compare(password, password_hash) → FAIL
    end

    rect rgb(255,235,235)
    Note over FE,R: 3. Record Failed Attempt (Counter Continues from 5)

    AUTH->>SVC: record_failed_attempt(user_id)
    SVC->>DB: UPDATE users<br/>SET failed_login_attempts = failed_login_attempts + 1,<br/>    last_failed_login_at = NOW()<br/>WHERE id = ? RETURNING failed_login_attempts
    DB-->>SVC: { failed_login_attempts: 6 }
    SVC-->>AUTH: { failed_login_attempts: 6 }
    Note right of AUTH: 6 > SOFT_LOCK_THRESHOLD(5) — no new Redis SET<br/>6 < HARD_LOCK_THRESHOLD(10) — no hard lock<br/>remaining_hard_lock_attempts = 10 - 6 = 4

    AUTH-->>GW: 401 { error_code: "INVALID_CREDENTIALS", remaining_hard_lock_attempts: 4 }
    GW-->>FE: 401 { error_code: "INVALID_CREDENTIALS", remaining_hard_lock_attempts: 4 }
    Note over FE: UI: "4 more failed attempts before your account is permanently locked."
    end
